# HTTP response headers for the Cloudflare Pages PRODUCTION deploy.
#
# INERT on the GitHub Pages testing host (GitHub Pages does not read _headers); it takes effect
# only on the Cloudflare Pages deploy. Like _redirects, this file MUST be listed in _config.yml
# `include:` or Jekyll silently drops underscore-prefixed files from _site (then it never ships).
#
# After the Cloudflare cutover, verify once in the browser (DevTools -> Console) that no page
# logs a CSP violation. If anything is unexpectedly blocked, switch the header name to
# `Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only` to observe without enforcing, fix, then switch back.
#
# CSP is strict 'self': the site self-hosts its CSS, fonts, images, icons, and its one script
# (the form-field init at /assets/js/form-handling.js). JSON-LD is type="application/ld+json"
# (a data block, not governed by script-src). The lead form POSTs to AgencyBloc (form-action).
# There are NO iframes, inline styles/scripts, data: URIs, or third-party resource loads — every
# external host on the site is an <a href> link, which CSP does not police.
#
# CHANGE CONTROL: enabling Cloudflare Web Analytics / Turnstile / any embed or tracker adds a
# resource load that this CSP will block. Update the relevant directive HERE FIRST, in lockstep
# with the privacy-copy switch (canon Switch Registry; flagged-items 5.2 / 5.3). A blocked
# tracker is the fail-safe, not the goal — wire the CSP and the Privacy Policy together so a new
# tracker can't ship while the copy still says "no tracking", and vice-versa.
#   - Cloudflare Web Analytics  -> script-src + connect-src  https://static.cloudflareinsights.com / cloudflareinsights.com
#   - Turnstile                 -> script-src + frame-src    https://challenges.cloudflare.com
#   - a Google Static Maps image-> img-src                   https://maps.googleapis.com
#   - Google Tag Manager / GA4  -> script-src + connect-src + img-src  https://www.googletagmanager.com https://www.google-analytics.com https://*.google-analytics.com
#   - Facebook (Meta) Pixel     -> script-src + connect-src + img-src  https://connect.facebook.net https://www.facebook.com
# GOTCHA for GTM + the Pixel: each also ships an INLINE bootstrap <script>, which strict
# script-src 'self' blocks — allowing the domains is NOT enough. Give that snippet a per-response
# nonce or a sha256 hash (or move it to an external /assets/js file), or loosen script-src. Treat
# that as part of the same change-control step, never a quick inline paste.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self'; img-src 'self'; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; manifest-src 'self'; form-action 'self' https://app.agencybloc.com; frame-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=()
